<title>PORTUGAL: Green shoe in EDP privatisation exercised.</title>
<headline>Green shoe in EDP privatisation exercised.</headline>
<dateline>LISBON 1997-06-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>The &quot;green shoe&quot; representing 16.36 million shares in the privatisation of utility EDP-Electricidade de Portugal was exercised, an official of global coordinator Banco Portugues de Investimento said.  </p>
<p>Incorporating the green shoe, 12.687 million shares were distributed in the direct sale in Portugal, 31.020 million shares in the U.S., 22.44 million in Britain and 14.025 million in Europe and the rest of the world.</p>
<p>In total, 80.172 million shares were placed in the direct sale.</p>
<p>The government earned more than $2.0 billion from the privatisation of a 30 percent stake in EDP on Monday.</p>
